name: Aztec restoration #1.5
description: This is a detail from plate 53 of the 16th century aztec text the Codex Borgia, depicting the deity Xochipilli (Prince of Flowers) with his distinctive red and white face paint. He is depicted as a deer, with the 20 day signs attached to his body. The five day signs on the white banner (Death, Deer, Rabbit, Water and Dog) are each linked to a cardinal directions. The meaning of the picture is not known.
